<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I am doing some processing of some org documents and after loading the file into non interactive buffers I set org-mode before doing the processing.</p> <p>The code runs along this line</p> <pre><code> (with-temp-buffer (insert-file-contents-literally full-filename) (org-mode) ... </code></pre> <p>I suspect that running <code>org-mode</code> after I open the file is the reason why it is slow.</p> <p>Can the same processing be done so long as the files is not interactively edited? The task involved is a read-only task?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/vfclists"> /u/vfclists </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w0rzyj/is_it_necessary_for_buffer_to_be_switched_to/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w0rzyj/is_it_necessary_for_buffer_to_be_switched_to/">[comments]</a></span>